<h1>Weather Station Instruments</h1>

<h2>Air Temperature and Relative Humidity Probe:</h2>
<%=image_tag("weatherstation/temp_hum.png", class: "pull-right")%>
<p>The HMP50-ET is a temperature and relative humidity sensor manufactured by Vaisala. It measures air temperature with a 1000 ohm platinum
  resistance thermometer (PRT), and relative humidity with a capacitive chip. A radiation shield is used to cover the probe to protect it from sunlight.</p>

<h3>Specifications:</h3>

<p><strong>Temperature</strong></p>

<ul>
    <li>Measurement Range: -25° to +60°C</li>

    <li>Accuracy of +/- 0.8 º C </li>
  </ul>

<p><strong>Relative Humidity</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Operating Range: 0 to 98% RH</li>
    <li>Accuracy: ±3% (0-90% RH); ±5% (90-98% RH)   </li>
  </ul>
  <hr />
<h2>Solar Radiation Sensor:</h2>
<%=image_tag("weatherstation/solar_rad.png", class: "pull-right")%>
<p>The CS305-ETM is a pyranometer manufactured by Apogee Instruments. It measures shortwave radiation using a silicon photovoltaic detector.
  The range of the sensor is 300 to 1100 nanometers, which encompasses most of the shortwave radiation that reaches the Earth&#8217;s surface. </p>


<h3>Specifications:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Accuracy: ±5% for daily total radiation </li>
    <li>Range: 0 to 2000 W m-2 </li>
    <li>Operating Temperature: -40° to +55°C </li>
    <li>Relative Humidity: 0 to 100% </li>
    <li>Output of 0.2 mV per Wm-2 </li>
  </ul>
  <hr />
<h2>Rain Gage:</h2>
<%=image_tag("weatherstation/rain.png", class: "pull-right")%>
<p>The TE525-ET tipping bucket rain gage is manufactured by Texas Electronics. It measures precipitation in 0.01 inch increments.
  The precipitation is funneled into a bucket that tips when filled to the calibrated level of 0.01 inches; the magnet connected to the tipping mechanism activates a switch as the bucket tips. This momentary switch closure is counted by the pulse-counting circuitry of the weather station’s data logger. </p>

<h3>Specifications:</h3>
  <ul>
      <li>Temperature: 0° to +50°C</li>
      <li>Resolution: 1 tip</li>
      <li>Rainfall per tip: 0.01&#8221; (0.254 mm)</li>
      <li>Orifice diameter: 6.06&#8221; (15.4 cm)</li>
      <li>Accuracy is ±1% at rates up to 1&#8221;/hr or +/- accuracy @ 2” per hr (50.8mm per hr) or less</li>
  </ul>
  <hr />
<h2>Anemometer and Vane:</h2>
<%=image_tag("weatherstation/wind.png", class: "pull-right")%>
<p>The 034B-ETM Windset is an instrument that combines a 3-cup anemometer and a wind vane. It is made of aluminum and its purpose is to measure wind speed and direction.
  The wind speed is measured as the cups rotate- opening and closing a reed switch at a rate corresponding to wind speed.
  The vane position is conveyed by a 10K ohm potentiometer with the output voltage related to wind direction.</p>

<h3>Specifications:</h3>

<p><strong>Anemometer</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Range: 0 to 110 mph (0 to 50 m/s) </li>
    <li>Threshold: 0.9 mph (0.4 m/s) </li>
    <li>Accuracy: ±0.25 mph (0.11 m/s) when less than 22.7 mph (10.1 m/s) or ±1.1% of true when greater than 22.7 mph (10.1 m/s)</li>
  </ul>

<p><strong>Vane</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Mechanical range: 360° </li>

    <li>Electrical range: 356° </li>

    <li>Threshold: 0.9 mph (0.4 m/s) </li>

    <li>Accuracy: ±4° </li>

    <li>Damping ratio: 0.25 </li>

    <li>Resolution: 0.5° </li>
    </ul>
   <hr />
<h2>Solar Panel:</h2>
<%=image_tag("weatherstation/solar_panel.png", class: "pull-right")%>
<p>A 10-Watt solar panel powers the weather station, charging a 7-Ahr rechargeable battery.</p>

<h3>Specifications:</h3>
    <ul>
    <li>Current at peak: 0.59 A </li>
    <li>Voltage at peak: 16.8 V </li>
   </ul>
  <hr />
<h2>Datalogger:</h2>
<%=image_tag("weatherstation/datalogger1.png", class: "pull-right")%>
<%=image_tag("weatherstation/datalogger2.png", class: "pull-right")%>
<p>An environmental enclosure (the white case) protects a CR1000M module and the battery. The datalogger is designed to both control the functions of the weather station instruments and record measurements. A spectrum spread radio then transmits the information to a nearby modem and is connected to the campus system.</p>

<h3>Specifications:</h3>
 <ul>
    <li>Analog inputs: 16 single-ended or 8 differential, individually configured </li>

    <li>Pulse counters: 2 </li>

    <li>Switched voltage excitations: 3 </li>

    <li>Control/digital ports: 8</li>

    <li>RS-232 port: 1</li>

    <li>CS I/O port: 1 </li>

    <li>Scan rate: 100 Hz </li>

    <li>Burst mode: 1500 Hz </li>

    <li>Analog volt. resolution: to 0.33 uV </li>

    <li>A/D bits: 13 </li>

    <li>Programming: CRBasic</li>

    <li>Data Storage: Table </li>

    <li>Telecommunications: PakBus </li>
   </ul>
